Minister of Public Enterprises, Lynne Brown, addressed the media from Parliament's Imbizo Centre on Friday, regarding the reappointment of Brian Molefe as Eskom CEO. Watch below.&nbsp; In April, Brown turned down Eskom's proposal to give its former CEO and newly-sworn in MP Brian Molefe a R30m pension payout.&nbsp;Commentators believe a 'compromise' has been reached after it was announced on Friday that Molefe is set to return to Eskom as CEO on Monday, as the board had rescinded his application for early retirement.&nbsp;Watch the below:&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.